content:
✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: It's look nice, maybe a reeverses mode is also possible. 
it seems great

Fun CoC puzzle:
- Line 1 should be "An integer [[N]] for the number of strings to be searched". When you say "digit of strings", in a puzzle about finding digits in strings, it could get confusing.
- Or, you can not have an N at all, since every puzzle is 5 strings.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I accept this contribution because I think it corresponds perfectly to a COC

HI lilToshi,
thanks for your contribution!
Some thoughts:
- Wording: in the Goal part: remove 'outputs', you must search strings for capitalized letters,
  not string outputs. 
- Highlighting in the input part: as it is now it suggests that both N and S are input, but only N is. 
  So I think it should be something like 'An integer "N":  the number of strings to process'
- Wording: still in the input part: the output does not decipher the strings, the code should 
  decipher the strings and output the results

The same contribution has been uploaded twice. Please remove one of them. Link to the other:
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/48921be0d618fdf6f4073c26b3e60cee700b5

Goal section
* Suggest to add "from that string" after "there is no output".

* Suggest to change "Input lines" to "Each input line" for the sake of clarity.

Input section
* Do you mean "number" instead of "digit"?

Output section
* Suggest to add "in the same order as the input strings".

Constraints section
* The upper limit of N is not a realistic reflection of actual test coverage. Suggest to lower it to 10.

Cases
* Suggest to vary N among the cases. Otherwise you may as well not provide N as an input if N is always 5.

Thanks.
